Looking at this, the code has no unused variables, floats, deprecated calls, unused functions, or long lines — so the warnings come from Elixir's newer type checker, whose known false-positive spot here is the `with/else` in `parse_uri` (the struct-match failure feeds the URI struct into `else` alongside the algorithm error tuple, and `parsed.query` is accessed after refinement). I'll rewrite `parse_uri` as an explicit nested `case` that binds `query` directly in the pattern, which removes both warning sources while keeping behavior (and all tests) identical.

